taset entry is stored as a semantic chunk with metadata attributes including: Category Severity level Risk level Action type (support or escalate) DSM-5-TR derived source Confidence level This structure enables accurate and safe retrieval through LangChain-based RAG pipelines. 8. Ethical Alignment and Safety Assurance The dataset strictly follows DSM-5-TR ethical guidance by: Avoiding diagnosis or treatment claims Supporting only mild depressive symptoms Escalating high-risk cases immediately Encouraging professional help when needed MindEase operates as a low-intensity emotional support system, not a replacement for therapy or clinical services. 9. Summary The MindEase RAG dataset comprehensively covers all DSM-5-TR depressive disorders, while providing detailed therapeutic content only for ethically appropriate conditions. This design ensures scientific validity, ethical safety, and effective support for individuals experiencing low to mild depression.', '[0.0075265123,-0.007656318,0.04488066,0.07702467,0.016135545,0.0022158392,0.032780875,0.14724088,-0.017248616,-0.073451586,-0.018256364,-0.048152216,-0.03686939,0.021808853,0.08157571,0.047947116,0.14777881,-0.0001444999,-0.03192104,0.07274508,0.09951984,0.10248557,0.028531643,-0.00069357984,-0.025943045,0.013534723,-0.01246176,0.020393124,0.0057469597,0.027473763,-0.023681685,0.088033944,0.032563984,0.08929004,0.015428506,0.016119627,-0.022822723,0.03289199,-0.00015898007,-0.0067731887,-0.04265996,-0.050358817,-0.013941396,-0.04670292,0.034293298,-0.06743065,-0.06972086,0.032818638,-0.059210554,-0.0063040373,-0.016133813,0.039500542,0.062726736,0.101893626,-0.0421571,-0.018999461,0.014016116,0.024541242,0.0014134706,0.03866208,-0.061006423,-0.018081445,0.031039638,-0.04793974,0.031425733,0.10321619,-0.042749222,-0.027534261,0.090807036,0.0543055,-0.103404015,-0.1052973,-0.009036842,0.035188083,-0.061757874,0.022501642,0.044071924,-0.022549016,0.049391497,0.0014217914,-0.053316433,0.056512076,0.119301856,0.008539